----
3:84. Say: 'In Allah we believe,
and what has been sent down unto us, and to Abraham, Ishmael, Isaac, Jacob, and the tribes, and what was vouchsafed to Moses and Jesus and to the prophets from their Lord:
We differ between none of them, and to Him we wholly submit?
----
3:85. And whoever seeks anything
but complete submission to Allah as a religion shall never have it accepted of him, while in the afterlife he shall be of those utterly ruined.
----
3:86. How should Allah guide a people who disbelieved after they had believed and acknowledged the Messenger was true, and the unmistakably clear proofs had reached them?
And Allah guides not the people of the wrongdoers.
----
3:87. Those, their requital is that the curse of Allah and the angels and all mankind together shall be upon them,
----
3:88. Ever to abide therein:
Never shall the chastisement be lightened from them, nor they be given any respite.
----
3:89. Save those who repent at once after doing so heinous as that, and mend their ways;
For verily Allah is all-forgiving, all-compassionate.
----
3:90. Truly those who commit unbelief after having believed,
then even increase in unbelief most foul, never shall their repentance be accepted, and those are the hopelessly lost.
----
3:91. Verily those who disbelieve and die disbelieving,
an earthful of gold would not be accepted from a single one of them. were he to pay it all in ransom:
Those shall have a painful chastisement, and they have no one who may help.
